725087f-a.title: Queens: 20th Avenue - 33rd Street
725087f-a.text:
Twentieth Ave., west of 33rd Street, showing at the left a one-
story garage located at the Southwest Corner of 31st Street and Twentieth
Avenue. At the right is the property of the Astoria iight, Heat and Power
Company.
May 1929.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.

725088f-b.title: Queens: 20th Avenue - 33rd Street
725088f-b.text:
Twentieth Ave., south side, between 35th (right) and 33rd Street
(left) and 33rd Street (left) showing the George Kouwenhoven farmhouse.
This is a nnear view; the house faces on Old Bowery Road. It was demolished
in May 1929. This is a set of three views. See Twentieth Road for more
dats.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection. Views 1,2&3.
